To qualify for a certificate of approval, an applicant shall satisfy the Secretary that:
The proposed private group home is consistent with the State plan;
The applicant is a proper person to receive a certificate of approval;
The proposed private group home is appropriate for the stated purpose;
The proposed private group home meets or, on completion, will meet the licensing requirements of Subtitle 9 of this title;
The proposed private group home meets or, on completion, will meet all of the general zoning requirements that apply to the site and that relate to:
The height and size of any buildings that are involved;
The land that may be covered or occupied;
The open space requirements;
The density requirements; and
The use of any land or buildings; and
The applicant's facilities meet the federal regulation requirements on program accessibility (45 C.F.R. §§ 84.21 through 84.23).
